  "doc_id": "22573",
  "text": "The Christian Congregation of Jehovah's Witnesses was established in 1872 in the USA. Nowadays, it has about eight million of followers. JW do not receive blood products. They equate blood transfusion with blood consumption, which would be contrary to biblical recommendations in Genesis (\"Only flesh with its soul -its blood -you must not eat. \"), Leviticus (\"You must not eat the blood of any sort of flesh, because the soul of every sort of flesh is its blood. Anyone eating it will be cut off.\") and Deuteronomy (\"Just be firmly resolved not to eat the blood, because the blood is the life, and you must not eat the life with the flesh.\"). The faithful see refusal of blood transfusion as an act of obedience to God, which will guarantee them eternal life [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
